Primitives
• Very similar to C
– Common across all platforms (JVM to the
rescue!)
– No unsigned variants
• Java Primitives
boolean true/false long 8 bytes
byte 1 byte float 4 bytes
char 2 bytes (unicode) double 8 bytes
int 4 bytes
– Generally used as local variables, parameters
and instance variables (property of an object)
